      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou1-noncannulated-primary",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "FEA model credibly predicts compression-bending QoIs for non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct",
      "description": "The FEA modeling ensemble (FDA reference model, Ansys implementation, DePuy Synthes proprietary solver) credibly predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading. All three quantities of interest fall within the pre-specified ±10% acceptance band and the normalised error metric E/uval remains below 1.96 across all N=11 experimental replicates from two independent laboratories. The claim scope is restricted to the validated loading mode (compression-bending), the validated geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm diameter), and the validated material lot; extrapolation to cannulated variants or fatigue loading is outside this claim.",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory submission demonstrating model credibility sufficient for a Medium model-risk, Medium decision-consequence COU under ASME V&V 40-2018.",
      "scope": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, ASTM F1717 static compression-bending, N=11 constructs, two laboratories, three QoIs"
